    "Zong Fuli, also known as Kelly, is the chairman and CEO of beverage giant Hangzhou Wahaha Group.",
    "The company, started by her late father Zong Qinghou in 1987, is best known for its purified water and milk-based drinks.",
    "Kelly was vice chairman and CEO before the elder Zong died in February 2024, and officially took over in August after resolving an internal dispute where some shareholders questioned her leadership.",
    "Kelly has been trying to attract younger and health-conscious consumers with newer offerings like energy drinks and tea-based beverages.",
    "In 2025, she was sued in Hong Kong over $2.1 billion worth of trust assets by three plaintiffs who claim to be her half siblings."
